and anticipation outweigh unorganized? But not open to new ideas is a problem for long-distance where changing conditions.\n\nI think Candidate B's stress handling and conscientiousness are key for long flights; memory for numbers is a specific technical weakness but could be mitigated with checklists. However communication issues are serious.\n\nCandidate C's quick decision and calmness are top for emergencies; communication difficulty is a problem but maybe less severe than memory issues? Egocentric and unwilling to learn are concerning.\n\nOverall, I might favor Candidate C because decision-making under pressure and calmness are paramount, and technical understanding is good. Communication can be trained; egocentric may be mitigated by crew culture. Not willing to further education is a concern but maybe not immediate.\n\nThus I will vote Candidate C.\n\nNow produce public message summarizing evaluation and vote."}
